h1. {color:#6366f1}Prompt2Test{color} — Project Overview

{tip:title=What is Prompt2Test?}
An AI-powered test case generation and browser automation platform. QA engineers describe what they want to test in plain English — the AI agent authors a test plan, spins up a live browser, and executes it end-to-end.
{tip}

----

h2. Key Metrics

|| 18 || 5 || 4 || 3 || 4 || 2 || 3 || 1 || {color:#16a34a}15{color} ||
| AWS Services | GitHub Repos | UI Screens | CodePipelines | Environments | ECR Repos | Lambda Fns | AgentCore | Days to Build |

----

{toc:minLevel=2|maxLevel=3}

----

h2. 1. End-to-End Flow

{panel:borderColor=#e2e8f0|bgColor=#f8fafc}
|| QA Engineer || -> || React UI || -> || Bedrock AgentCore || -> || AI generates plan || -> || ECS Fargate || -> || Playwright MCP || -> || Live view (noVNC) || -> || PASS / FAIL ||
| types a prompt | | Amplify hosted | | Claude Sonnet 4.5 | | structured steps | | spins up on demand | | executes in browser | | streamed to UI | | saved to Aurora |
{panel}

----

h2. 2. UI Screens — Built & Deployed

{section}
{column:width=25%}
{panel:title=Agent|borderColor=#7c3aed|bgColor=#faf5ff}
Pick a service, describe the test scenario in plain English. AI generates a structured test plan. Review steps, then execute with a live browser.

{status:colour=Green|title=Built}
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=25%}
{panel:title=Inventory|borderColor=#2563eb|bgColor=#eff6ff}
Browse all saved test cases by environment and service. Search semantically via pgvector. View last run result, re-run, edit, or delete.

{status:colour=Green|title=Built}
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=25%}
{panel:title=Config|borderColor=#0d9488|bgColor=#f0fdfa}
Manage services (name + URL per env), test accounts (credentials per env), and team members. All stored in DynamoDB.

{status:colour=Green|title=Built}
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=25%}
{panel:title=Admin|borderColor=#ea580c|bgColor=#fff7ed}
Create/delete users, manage Cognito groups (teams), assign users to teams. Visible only to users in the {{admin}} group.

{status:colour=Green|title=Built}
{panel}
{column}
{section}

----

h2. 3. Feature Coverage

|| Feature || Description || Status ||
| AI Test Plan Generation | QA types a natural language prompt. Claude Sonnet 4.5 generates a structured plan with actions and expected outcomes. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Live Browser Automation | Playwright MCP executes test steps in a real Chromium browser. ECS Fargate task spins up on demand. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Live Browser View (noVNC) | Watch the browser execute in real-time via embedded noVNC iframe. Pop-out button opens a full window. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Test Replay | Re-execute a saved test case from Inventory without re-generating the plan. Uses stored replay script. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Test Case Inventory | Save, edit, delete test cases. Filter by environment and service. View last run result per test case. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Semantic Search | pgvector + Titan Embed Text v2 enables similarity search across test cases. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Service Config Management | Add services and URLs per environment via the UI. Stored in DynamoDB, read by AI agent. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Test Account Management | Store test account credentials per environment per team in DynamoDB. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Multi-Team Support | Teams are Cognito groups. Each team has isolated services, accounts, and test cases. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Multi-Environment | dev / qa / uat / prod. Config, accounts, and test cases scoped per environment. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Admin Panel | Create/delete Cognito users, manage team groups, assign users to teams. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Auth & Access Control | Cognito User Pool login. Identity Pool grants scoped IAM permissions. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| CI/CD — 4 Pipelines | Amplify auto-deploys UI. 3 CodePipelines for Lambda, Agent, Playwright MCP. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Exploratory Mode | No service selected — agent runs in exploratory mode, navigating freely. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Run Records | Every execution stored as a run record with result, summary, timestamp. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Environment Promotion | Promote test cases DEV -> QA -> UAT -> PROD with \{service.KEY\} templates. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Config Template References | Plan steps use \{service.KEY\} instead of hardcoded URLs. Portable across envs. | {status:colour=Green|title=Complete} |
| Test Metrics Dashboard | Aggregate pass/fail rates, trends over time, most-run services. | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Planned} |
| Slack / Email Notifications | Notify team on test failure or completion. | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Planned} |
| Scheduled Test Runs | Schedule smoke tests on a cron (e.g. every deploy, nightly). | {status:colour=Yellow|title=Planned} |

----

h2. 4. Implementation Effort

{info:title=Built in 15 days by 1 engineer using AI-assisted development (Claude Code)}
12x faster than traditional approach (6 months with 4-5 engineers).
{info}

h3. Phase 1 — Infrastructure & AWS Setup

|| Feature || What was built || Effort || Complexity ||
| VPC + Networking | VPC, 2 public subnets, security groups for ECS + Aurora | 1 day | Low |
| Cognito Auth + Identity Pool | User Pool, Identity Pool, Cognito Groups, IAM auth role | 3 days | Medium |
| Aurora Serverless v2 + pgvector | Aurora PostgreSQL 16, RDS Data API, Secrets Manager, pgvector | 3 days | Medium |
| DynamoDB Config Table | prompt2test-config table, pk/sk schema, migrated from SSM | 2 days | Low |
| ECS Fargate Cluster + Task | ECS cluster, ARM64 task def (2vCPU/4GB), ECR repos | 2 days | Medium |
| CDK — Full IaC | All 18 AWS services as CDK TypeScript, one-command deploy | 3 days | High |
| *Phase 1 Subtotal* | | *14 days* | |

h3. Phase 2 — Backend: Lambda + Playwright MCP

|| Feature || What was built || Effort || Complexity ||
| Lambda — testcase-writer | Python Lambda for save/update/delete test cases and run records | 2 days | Medium |
| Lambda — testcase-reader | Python Lambda for list, fetch, semantic search via pgvector | 2 days | Medium |
| Playwright MCP Container | Playwright + noVNC + Chromium in Docker on ECS Fargate ARM64 | 3 days | High |
| *Phase 2 Subtotal* | | *7 days* | |

h3. Phase 3 — AI Agent (Bedrock AgentCore)

|| Feature || What was built || Effort || Complexity ||
| AgentCore Container + FastAPI | Python FastAPI on port 8080, /invocations + /ping endpoints | 2 days | Medium |
| Plan mode | Strands SDK agent generates conversational test plan | 2 days | Medium |
| Plan Scenario mode | Structured JSON output, service context injection | 3 days | High |
| Automate mode + ECS session | Spin up ECS task, connect to Playwright MCP, stream events | 3 days | Very High |
| Replay mode | Re-run saved test without re-generating plan | 1 day | Low |
| get_service_config tool | Strands @tool that reads service config from DynamoDB | 1 day | Low |
| *Phase 3 Subtotal* | | *12 days* | |

h3. Phase 4 — React Frontend (4 Screens)

|| Feature || What was built || Effort || Complexity ||
| Auth + Layout + Routing | Cognito login, JWT group parsing, env switcher, team-aware routing | 2 days | Medium |
| Agent Page | Service picker, chat panel, step table, live browser panel, streaming | 5 days | Very High |
| Inventory Page | Test case list/filter, DynamoDB service loader, run/replay/delete | 2 days | Medium |
| Config Page (DynamoDB) | Services + accounts CRUD per team per env | 3 days | High |
| Admin Page | User create/delete, Cognito group management | 2 days | Medium |
| *Phase 4 Subtotal* | | *14 days* | |

h3. Phase 5 — CI/CD + Documentation

|| Feature || What was built || Effort || Complexity ||
| 3 CodePipelines | Lambda, Agent, Playwright MCP — GitHub -> CodeBuild -> ECR | 2 days | Medium |
| Amplify CI/CD | Amplify hosting, auto-deploy on push, CloudFront CDN | 1 day | Low |
| Architecture Docs | Architecture diagram, ADRs, Deployment Guide | 2 days | Low |
| Handover & Overview | CI/CD Handover Guide, Project Overview page | 1 day | Low |
| *Phase 5 Subtotal* | | *6 days* | |

----

h2. 5. AI Acceleration Comparison

|| Phase || No AI (~6 months, 4-5 team) || Moderate AI (~2 months, 2 team) || {color:#16a34a}Aggressive AI (15 days, 1 engineer){color} ||
| Infrastructure + AWS CDK | 4-5 weeks | 2-3 weeks | *3 days* |
| Backend — Lambda + Playwright | 3-4 weeks | 1-2 weeks | *2 days* |
| AI Agent — AgentCore + Strands | 6-8 weeks | 3-4 weeks | *4 days* |
| React Frontend — 4 Screens | 5-6 weeks | 2-3 weeks | *5 days* |
| CI/CD + Documentation | 2-3 weeks | 1 week | *1 day* |
| *Total* | *~6 months* | *~2 months* | {color:#16a34a}*15 days*{color} |

{note:title=12x Faster}
6 months -> 15 days. Same production-ready output, fraction of the calendar time.
{note}

